{"openapi":"3.0.1","info":{"title":"Customer API","description":"# Introduction\n  API for Echo Customers. Customer can request for Quotes.\n\n**Supported Authorization strategies:**\n* Basic Auth\n\n  All API operations require an Authorization header with content Basic\n  followed by **client_id** and **client_secret** in encoded string.\n\n* OAuth 2.0\n\n **`API Authentications:`** All API operations require an access token to be\n passed in the Authorization Header for each request. The token type is an\n OAuth 2.0 Bearer token. To get the token you have to call the Authentication\n operation of this API and provide **client_id** and **client_secret**.\n\n **`Access Token Lifecycle:`** When you receive an Access Token, it will be valid\n  for a 10 hours. During this time it is not necessary to request a new token for\n  subsequent requests. Simply reuse the existing token to access API resources until the\n  token expires. Once the token has expired, a new token must be requested.\n  An invalid or expired token will be indicated by an HTTP 401 Unauthorized Status Code.\n\n  **`Access Token Request Rate Limiting:`** The Access Token should be used for the lifetime\n  of the token until it has expired. Partners requesting new tokens multiple times in an hour\n  may be subject to rate limiting.\n\n  **`API Request Rate Limiting:`** Please do not exceed more than 3 requests per second.\n  Partners who exceed this limit may be subject to rate limiting.","version":"v2.1.3-main","contact":{"name":"Echo Global Logistics","url":"https://www.echo.com","email":"info@echo.com"}},"servers":[{"description":"SwaggerHub API Auto Mocking","url":"https://virtserver.swaggerhub.com/echogl/Customer_API_OAuth_Public/v2.1.3-main"},{"url":"https://customerapi.echo.com","description":"Production server"}],"tags":[{"name":"quotes","description":"Used for creating and retrieving quotes."},{"name":"CORS","description":"CORS enabled API resources."}],"x-tagGroups":[{"name":"Core APIs","tags